cs.FL, cs.DS, cs.LO, cs.CC, cs.PL

Reasoning: 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is the most likely category as the paper deals with regular languages and automata.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper discusses the decidability and complexity of a problem.
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is relevant as the paper deals with the separability of languages, which can be seen as a logical problem.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is relevant as the paper discusses the PSpace-completeness of a problem.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with the properties of a specific type of automata.
